    questionText: 'Two parabolas are given by \\( C_1\\colon y = x^2 \\) and \\( C_2\\colon y = x - x^2 + \\dfrac{a}{2} \\), where \\( a > 0 \\).\n\n(i) Show that \\( C_1 \\) and \\( C_2 \\) intersect where \\( 2x^2 - x - \\dfrac{a}{2} = 0 \\), and find the coordinates of the two intersection points in terms of \\( a \\). [3 marks]\n\n(ii) At the right-hand intersection point, find the gradients of the tangents to \\( C_1 \\) and \\( C_2 \\). Show that these tangents are perpendicular if and only if \\( a = 1 \\). [5 marks]\n\n(iii) Find the area enclosed between \\( C_1 \\) and \\( C_2 \\) and express it in terms of \\( a \\). [4 marks]\n\n(iv) When \\( a = 1 \\), find the equations of the two tangents at the right-hand intersection point and find the area of the triangle formed by these tangents and the \\( y \\)-axis. [2 marks]',
