          workingLatex: '\\text{base} = \\frac{7+\\sqrt{5}}{8} - \\frac{-3-\\sqrt{5}}{8} = \\frac{10+2\\sqrt{5}}{8} = \\frac{5+\\sqrt{5}}{4}',
          explanation: 'The triangle has vertices at \\( (x_R, y_R) \\) (where the tangents meet) and the two \\( y \\)-intercepts on the \\( y \\)-axis. The base along the \\( y \\)-axis has length \\( \\frac{5+\\sqrt{5}}{4} \\) and the perpendicular distance from \\( (x_R, y_R) \\) to the \\( y \\)-axis is \\( x_R = \\frac{1+\\sqrt{5}}{4} \\). Area \\( = \\frac{1}{2} \\cdot \\frac{5+\\sqrt{5}}{4} \\cdot \\frac{1+\\sqrt{5}}{4} = \\frac{(5+\\sqrt{5})(1+\\sqrt{5})}{32} = \\frac{10 + 6\\sqrt{5}}{32} = \\frac{5 + 3\\sqrt{5}}{16} \\).'
